cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.IT

This paper deals with the design of differentially private algorithms for data analysis, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of cryptography (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), databases (cs.DB), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and information theory (cs.IT). The paper specifically focuses on dynamically growing databases, which suggests that the sub-categories of databases and data structures and algorithms are particularly relevant. However, the use of machine learning and differential privacy techniques also makes the sub-categories of machine learning and cryptography likely.
